Kwa-Zulu Natal police are appealing to the public to help
locate the man who has information on a political killing. Police Spokesman Brigadier Jay Naicker said that on 18
November, councillor Sibusiso Maphumlo was shot and killed in Umlazi, Kwa-Zulu
Natal. Maphumlo was allegedly sitting in his car when he came
under a hail of bullets. “A case of murder was opened at the Umlazi Police Station
and was assigned to the Political Task Team for investigation,” Naicker said. “Anyone with information on his identity or whereabouts
is requested to contact the investigating officer, Sergeant Dlamini on 082 458
5297 or Crime Stop on 0860 10111,” he also said.